P(\overline{A}\cap \overline{B})=1-P(A \cup B).  \qquad\text{(Equation 1)}
P(A\cup B)=P(A)+P(B)-P(A\cap B)=P(A)+P(B)-P(A)P(B)  \qquad\text{(Equation 2)}
P(\overline{A}\cap \overline{B})=1-(P(A)+P(B)-P(A)P(B))=1-P(A)-P(B)+P(A)P(B).
1-P(A)-P(B)+P(A)P(B)=(1-P(A))(1-P(B))=P(\overline{A})P(\overline{B}),
